725145f-a.title: Queens: 26th Avenue - 4th Street
725145f-a.text:
26th Ave., north side, east of 4th Street, showing in the center,
to the east of the Weisberg-Baer sash and door factory (left),the John
J. Halsey house. This house was demolished prior to 1928. A. L. Hatch
was the owner in 1891.
1922.
Eugene L. Ambruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

724975f-a.title: Queens: 4th Street - 26th Avenue
724975f-a.text:
4th Street, east side, between 27th and 26th Avenues,
showing an old home about 150 feet back of the main building
line. The house appears in Wolverton's 1891 atlas, but its
ownership is not given.
P. L. Sperr  March 13, 1931
NO REERODUCTION:S

725146f-a.title: Queens: 26th Avenue - 4th Street
725146f-a.text:
26th Avenue, south side, east of 4th Street, showing the

P. L. Sperr  March 13, 1931
